```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "resources": {
      "nodes": 1,
      "tasks_per_node": 8,
      "cpus_per_task": 16,
      "memory": 0,
      "gpus": 8
    },
    "modules": {
      "rocm": "5.4.2",
      "ucx": "1.13.1",
      "ompi": "4.1.4"
    },
    "software": {
      "singularity": "lammps_2022.5.04_130.sif",
      "lammps": "/opt/lammps/bin/lmp"
    }
  }
}
```

This script runs a SLURM job that uses the LAMMPS simulation software. It uses Singularity to containerize the LAMMPS environment and runs the simulations on 8 GPUs. The script also specifies the necessary resources, including nodes, tasks per node, CPUs per task, memory, and GPUs. It loads specific modules for ROCm, UCX, and OpenMPI. The script runs multiple simulations with different parameters and input files, saving the results to a temporary directory before copying them to the working directory.
